On Thursday, U.S. President Joe Biden signed a bill into law increasing the debt limit by $2.5 trillion, averting a default temporarily. But as some analysts put it, with the skyrocketing public debt, the U.S. is inching closer to economic peril. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Cao Yi Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)